title: Louise, Princess Royal
summary: Louise, Princess Royal and Duchess of Fife VA, CI (Louise Victoria Alexandra Dagmar; 20 February 1867 â€“ 4 January 1931) was the third child and eldest daughter of King Edward VII and Queen Alexandra of the United Kingdom; she was a younger sister of King George V. Louise was given the title of Princess Royal in 1905.[2] Known by her shy and quiet personality, Louise remained a low-key member of the royal family throughout her life.[3]
